T*
(1. PURPOSE) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Evaluate and demonstrate how AI Code Agents can improve software delivery productivity and) Tj
T*
(quality while preserving enterprise controls for security, governance, compliance, and cost.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This proof of concept should be positioned as a controlled, low-cost developer workflow demo) Tj
T*
(using tools you already have: VS Code plus Codex. The live story should show three things:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Codex can work inside a real developer workflow from the IDE.) Tj
T*
(2. Codex can connect to MCP-style tools and external systems in a controlled way.) Tj
T*
(3. Codex can reduce delivery friction by speeding up common tasks such as code changes,) Tj
T*
(review preparation, validation, and deployment packaging.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The cleanest free demo is:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Start with a tiny sample app.) Tj
T*
(- Ask Codex to make a scoped change.) Tj
T*
(- Use MCP or local tools to inspect docs, files, or repo context.) Tj
T*
(- Package the app with Docker.) Tj
T*
(- Generate a PR-ready summary, risk list, and test notes.) Tj
T*
(- Show before/after cycle-time evidence using a stopwatch and a simple metrics sheet.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3. POC GOAL) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Prove that AI Code Agents can be adopted safely in a controlled enterprise model before any) Tj
T*
(broad rollout.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4. SUCCESS CRITERIA) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(PRODUCTIVITY) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Reduce time to complete a small feature or bug-fix task by 30 to 50 percent versus a) Tj
T*
(manual baseline.) Tj
T*
(- Reduce PR preparation time by 40 percent or more.) Tj
T*
(- Reduce time spent writing PR descriptions, test notes, and deployment instructions by 60) Tj
T*
(percent or more.) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
